FT  17 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Acquisition helps Sheriff to Pounds 161,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sheriff Holdings, which serves the contracting and construction industries,
slightly improved both turnover and profit in the six months ended March 31
1992.
Sales were up Pounds 3,000 to Pounds 4.7m and pre-tax profit rose Pounds
8,000 to Pounds 161,000. In the core plant business, hire turnover
experienced a marginal downturn, whereas sales of minor equipment and cabins
suffered more radically. Turnover was helped by a 3 1/2 month contribution
from Abelson Plant, purchased last December for Pounds 2.55m.
Since the purchase gearing had been reduced from 85 per cent to below 70 per
cent.
Earnings improved to 1.7p (1.5p). The interim dividend is lifted to 1p
(0.75p).
