<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUN 92 / BIS Annual Report: Last-ditch plan to save CIS trade
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BASLE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE BIS proposes a special clearing system as a last resort to prevent a
breakdown in trade among the republics of the Commonwealth of Independent
States,
It says the west needs to provide external finance while Russia and the
other republics make the transition to market economies. The most valuable
help, however, would be to allow the CIS free access to western markets.
Although the CIS's struggle to adjust is the most striking new feature of
the world economic landscape, the BIS says its debt does not seriously
threaten the financial system.
The rouble could be used to finance trade if it were stabilised and made
convertible, but plans by some republics to introduce their own currencies
risk eroding the rouble area.
</TEXT>
