<TEXT>
THE JAMAICAN and Russian governments are in negotiations about a dispute
over payment for bauxite ore shipped last year by the island to the former
Soviet Union.
Jamaican government officials say the ore was shipped under an agreement
with Raznoimport, a Soviet importing house based in Moscow. The contract,
