<TEXT>
GOLD extended early gains to close on the London bullion market at Dollars
343 a troy ounce, up Dollars 3.15 from Friday's finish on the back of
constructive technicals after an afternoon fix of Dollars 342.70. Dealers
said that the market appeared to be building a base of support around
Dollars 342, but concern remained over producer sell orders believed to be
in place around current levels. A break through Dollars 345-Dollars 346
would signal a sharp move to Dollars 350. Comex gold futures were firmer at
midday. 'Gold is holding its gains from last week so it looks good,' said
