FT  16 JUN 92 / International Company News: NZ white goods group shows sharp
growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FISHER and Paykel, the New Zealand white goods manufacturer, has reported an
88.4 per cent rise in net profits to NZDollars 8m (USDollars 4.3m) from
NZDollars 4.2m a year earlier, helped by strong growth in exports.
The company reported a 50 per cent advance in sales in Australia following
the opening of a factory in Queensland. This gives it 10 per cent of the
Australian market.
Continuing slack demand in New Zealand saw an 8 per cent drop in sales there
to NZDollars 331.1m.
Total export earnings, to Australia and the US, rose 40 per cent to
NZDollars 144.3m. Operating revenue was virtually unchanged at NZDollars
504.83m.
Directors said demand would remain low for the rest of the year. Tax was
NZDollars 3.76m (NZDollars 2.2m). Bottom-line profit was NZDollars 6.9m
against NZDollars 4.4m) last year.
Shareholders' funds were NZDollars 225.9m compared with NZDollars 224.9m a
year earlier. A total dividend of 8 cents a share is being recommended, up
from 10 cents.
