<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Brighter outlook at Welpac
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WELPAC, the hardware and electrical goods wholesaler and distributor,
incurred a loss of Pounds 305,000 pre-tax for the year to January 31.
That compared with pre-tax profits of Pounds 13,000 for 1990-91.
However, the year under review was one of reorganisation and strategic
development and in the second six months Welpac returned profits of Pounds
53,000 before tax and exceptional items compared with losses of Pounds
248,000 in the first half.
The full year loss, struck on turnover of Pounds 9.72m (Pounds 11.42m), took
account of exceptional costs of Pounds 110,000 (nil) for redundancy and
other reorganisation.
Interest charges took Pounds 209,000 more at Pounds 541,000 but over the
second half the charge was cut from Pounds 361,000 to Pounds 180,000.
Losses per share emerged at 0.45p (earnings 0.42p). However, reflecting the
recovery shown in the second half and expectations of a 'reasonable
out-turn' for the current year the company is returning to the dividend list
via a 0.2p payment.
Year-end gearing was reduced from 126 per cent to 44.6 per cent.
</TEXT>
