<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MOSCOW has given state guarantees paving the way for Bonn to resume
government export credits and revitalise trade between Germany and Russia,
the economics ministry said yesterday, Reuter reports from Bonn.
A Bonn official said Russia had provided the long-awaited documents to allow
the German government to grant its Hermes export guarantees. Trade between
Russia and Germany has virtually stalled since January when Bonn put a DM5bn
(Pounds 1.7bn) ceiling on export guarantees for the former Soviet Union.
Moscow had earlier failed to give its guarantee to either Germany's State
Reconstruction Bank or the German export credit organisation, saying this
was against its constitution. Bonn's first export guarantee of the year for
the former Soviet Union went to Ukraine in April.
